\section{IIW: Perceptual Shading Quality}
\label{sec:iiw_results}

IIW measures perceptual shading quality through pairwise human comparisons.
WHDR is the fraction of judgements with which the model's albedo ordering
disagrees.
\tabref{tab:iiw} shows results on the IIW test set, identical for all models.
Every row in the upper block is run zero-shot, except CRefNet's cited entry in
the lower block, which fine-tunes on the IIW training split and is marked
accordingly; CRefNet is also run locally, zero-shot, in the upper block, so the
two rows isolate the effect of that fine-tuning directly.

