    WHDR is not zero-shot; its locally run entry above is zero-shot.
    The upper block is run under our pipeline; the lower block is
    \emph{cited}: Ordinal Shading's own zero-shot Table~2 figure, and full-split
    IIW WHDR as reproduced by \mycite{yuan25texture}, Table~I, which is context
    rather than a head-to-head comparison (different test split and per-method
    protocol).
  }
  \label{tab:iiw}
